         <abstract>
            <p>Let R and S be positive integers with &lt;latex&gt;$R &lt; S$&lt;/latex&gt;. We shall call the simultaneous Diophantine equations x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - Ry&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = 1, z&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - Sy&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = 1 simultaneous Pell equations in R and S. Each such pair has the trivial solution (1, 0, 1) but some pairs have nontrivial solutions too. For example, if R = 11 and S = 56, then (199, 60, 449) is a solution. Using theorems due to Baker, Davenport, and Waldschmidt, it is possible to show that the number of solutions is always finite, and it is possible to give a complete list of them. In this paper we report on the solutions when &lt;latex&gt;$R &lt; S \leq 200$&lt;/latex&gt;.</p>
          </abstract>
